race.comment: CROWN LEGEND (3) returned from a spell last start over 1200m at Gilgandra and caught the eye late, getting up for second and making up around five lengths from the time they straightened. Has a terrible draw to contend with so probably goes back again but over the extra 100m can finish right over the top. TRIPLE TRIPLE (5) led all the way to salute over this distance at Taree two back. Took on a tougher race over 1200m at Gosford last time and found that beyond him. Better placed back up to 1300m in the country so watch for a return to form. The lightly raced AFRICAN DIAMOND (8) has enjoyed a let-up since just missing over 1450m at Muswellbrook on 28 November. Goes well when fresh so she is right in contention. PICKAXE (2) is a new arrival in the Connie Greig stable and is one for the exotics first-up from a four-month break. The lightly raced YACHT GIRL (12) has been freshened up since the first poor run of her career a month ago. Worth forgiving.
